leafpad
------------------------------------------
Leafpad is a simple GTK+ text editor that emphasizes simplicity. As 
development focuses on keeping weight down to a minimum, only the most 
essential features are implemented in the editor. Leafpad is simple to 
use, is easily compiled, requires few libraries, and starts up quickly.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-62
  libcairo2-1.8.8-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.20.6-1
  libgtk2.0_0-2.16.5-1
  libintl8-0.17-11
  libpango1.0_0-1.24.5-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-10
  automake1.10-1.10.2-10
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.9-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-1
  gnome-common-2.26.0-2
  intltool-0.40.6-1
  libtool-2.2.7a-14
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://tarot.freeshell.org/leafpad/

Canonical download:
  http://savannah.nongnu.org/download/leafpad/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack leafpad-0.8.16-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./leafpad-0.8.16-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/leafpad-0.8.16-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/leafpad-0.8.16-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 0.8.16-2 -----
Initial release for Cygwin 1.7.


